sentences: Childe Seguin (1811–1888) was a British and American opera singer who was part of the Seguin Troupe in America.
Ann Childe was born in London on 20 April 1811.
Childe was taking the lead in as Catherine in Lord Burghersh's opera of the same name in 1830.
Her future husband, Arthur Seguin (1809–1852) sang in support as Ismael.

Their troupe visited both Montreal and Toronto in Canada with W. H. Latham of the Theatre Royal in Drury Lane starting in 1839 and continuing over the next ten years.

The Seguin operatic troupe which had initially consisted of four to six singers went out of fashion in the late 1840s when audiences wanted their operas not in English but in the original language.
Seguin made her last appearance in an opera in 1852 at the Broadway Theatre in New York.
She died in New York in August 1888.
